    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-28T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-28T08:00:00-05:00" n="201"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.512351 Double/236: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Marriner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-28T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >March 28, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 28—10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>260. Senator Abel Gardey deposited with the Senate on March 26 the report in the
                    name of the Finance Committee concerning the double taxation treaty. This report
                    was ordered printed and appears <pb facs="0324" n="248" xml:id="pg_248"/> this
                    morning. The opinion of the Foreign Affairs Committee was requested on this
                    report and its report favorable to the conclusion of the Finance Committee was
                    deposited yesterday evening in the Senate by Senator Reynaldy.</p>
                <p>As Parliament may adjourn tomorrow I yesterday got in touch with M. Laval<note
                        n="46" xml:id="d201fn46">Pierre Laval, French Minister for Foreign
                        Affairs.</note> who informs me this morning that he is going himself before
                    the Senate this afternoon in an effort to put the treaty through.</p>
                <p>Texts of the reports which follow the lines of that of the Chamber’s Committee on
                    Finance transmitted with Embassy’s despatch 1664, March 1, 1935,<note n="47"
                        xml:id="d201fn47">Not printed.</note> will be forwarded by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marriner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
